      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BILLIES RAINBOW (4) was out of the placings last time but before that was an impressive winner (24.03) in a Rank Limit - Maiden at this track. Likely to improve sharply this time. WHO SHE RULES (7) turned in a better effort at this track last start, finishing second behind Ivory Quill (24.36) in a Bottom Up - Restricted Win. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. The form from her last run is stacking up nicely. Hard to beat again. NEW SHERIFF (3) found the going tougher but ran well to place over 425m at this track (24.18) in Mix 6/7. Scored at Shepparton in weaker company the previous run. The form out of the last run is proven to be strong. Expected to be in the finish again. POURING CHANDON (6) is coming off a slick 22.20 success on debut. Can measure up again.",
